title: Ann Arbor Floodplain
name: Ann Arbor Floodplain
description:
That portion of the river valley, adjacent to the
channel, which is built of sediments deposited during the present
geological / climatic regime. Based on statistically derived hydrologic
recurrence intervals, a portion of the land adjacent to the watercourse
experiences bank full overflow during flood stage episodes. created by the City of Ann Arbor Systems Planning using FEMA data.  Is now being updated by Systems Planning using newest FEMA data.
